Next to marrying my husband, it's my biggest regret in life.

538
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:36,730
- Madam. 
 - What?

539
00:36:38,510 --> 00:36:40,840
I'll be leaving.

540
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:46,360
Thank you for these. I appreciate them. They'll make good use of them.

541
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,650
Be careful with the steps there.

542
00:36:48,650 --> 00:36:51,560
I won't escort you. Get home safely.

543
00:36:52,310 --> 00:36:55,940
Thermal underwear? After dumping the child on you for ten years?

544
00:36:55,940 --> 00:36:59,580
Thermal underwear? Aigoo, what a joke.

545
00:37:05,090 --> 00:37:08,280
He wasn't dumped on me. I took him in.

546
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:11,050
Please don't be so harsh.

547
00:37:11,050 --> 00:37:15,230
She came to take Hae Joon many times.

548
00:37:15,230 --> 00:37:17,520
I didn't let him go.

549
00:37:28,070 --> 00:37:29,730
Auntie.

550
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:37,500
It's you! When did you get here?

551
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:40,300
- Are you coming home from school? 
 - Yes.

552
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,990
You're almost due! Why did you come all the way here?

553
00:37:43,990 --> 00:37:46,270
I could have come to you.

554
00:37:49,350 --> 00:37:51,610
The bus is still running.

555
00:37:52,370 --> 00:37:54,130
I have money.

556
00:38:02,140 --> 00:38:05,420
This is Joo Won's dad's money.

557
00:38:05,420 --> 00:38:07,200
Yes,

558
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:08,880
but I saved up my allowance.

559
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:12,190
Still, it isn't money you earned.

560
00:38:12,190 --> 00:38:14,630
You shouldn't waste it.

561
00:38:14,630 --> 00:38:16,480
Even though he gave it to you to spend,

562
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:20,690
you should repay it all when you're grown up.

563
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:23,820
I will.

564
00:38:23,820 --> 00:38:27,070
That's right, you should.

565
00:38:27,770 --> 00:38:32,080
Don't be a burden. Read the room.

566
00:38:32,740 --> 00:38:34,370
I know.

567
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:38,190
I'll take this cab.

568
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:23,110
   

569
00:39:30,890 --> 00:39:34,950
 Hey! Are you the child Mr. Yoon took in? 

570
00:39:34,950 --> 00:39:36,190
 Yes. 

571
00:39:36,190 --> 00:39:37,890
 Clean up nicely! 

572
00:39:37,890 --> 00:39:42,910
 If you don't do it right, Mr. Yoon will send you back home. 

573
00:39:49,610 --> 00:39:54,250
 Yet again. I've told you not to talk to him like that so many times. 

574
00:39:59,780 --> 00:40:01,190
 Don't cry. 

575
00:40:01,190 --> 00:40:05,930
 Even if you don't do things like this, you can stay here, Hae Joon. 

576
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:16,370
 Don't be a burden. Read the room. 

577
00:40:23,290 --> 00:40:25,800
Wow, looks delicious!

578
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:30,740
Dad got the best quality meat for you all.

579
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:35,240
I buy it once in a blue moon (rarely).

580
00:40:35,240 --> 00:40:37,100
Look at this color.

581
00:40:37,100 --> 00:40:40,960
If it's too well done, the fat's gone, and it isn't as tasty.

582
00:40:46,650 --> 00:40:48,450
What's wrong, Hae Joon? Don't you have an appetite?

583
00:40:48,450 --> 00:40:50,080
Should I make you some crab soybean soup?

584
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:53,040
No, this is good.

585
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:56,590
Scallion kimchi is perfect with pork belly.

586
00:40:56,590 --> 00:40:58,140
Here.

587
00:40:58,140 --> 00:41:01,720
Put some garlic in the wrap.

588
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:05,610
This garlic isn't your average garlic. It's from the Madam's mother's house.

589
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,190
Joo Won, what's going on with you?

590
00:41:11,650 --> 00:41:14,010
Stop picking at your food. It's unlike you. It's pork belly.

591
00:41:14,010 --> 00:41:15,640
Devour it like you usually do.

592
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:18,130
I don't always have an appetite.

593
00:41:18,130 --> 00:41:21,380
What? Do you even know what it's like not to have an appetite?

594
00:41:25,630 --> 00:41:27,780
We got into a fight.

595
00:41:31,290 --> 00:41:32,890
What happened?

596
00:41:33,940 --> 00:41:36,290
A fight about what?

597
00:41:36,290 --> 00:41:38,090
Did you throw a fit?

598
00:41:39,650 --> 00:41:43,190
Do you think I always throw a fit?

599
00:41:44,330 --> 00:41:47,870
I'm sure San Ha didn't get himself into trouble.

600
00:41:47,870 --> 00:41:50,940
Yes, I just gobble up meat,

601
00:41:50,940 --> 00:41:54,600
get in trouble, and Kim San Ha is a flawless person.

602
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:56,800
Good for you, good for you!

603
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,950
But still, eat some meat!

604
00:41:58,950 --> 00:42:00,990
- Dad got it for you! 
 - I'll talk to her.

605
00:42:00,990 --> 00:42:02,640
It's fine. Eat.

606
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:04,980
She'll be fine tomorrow.

607
00:42:04,980 --> 00:42:07,480
There's no need to wait until tomorrow.

608
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:09,750
I can make her feel better quickly.

609
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:16,960
Are you sleeping?

610
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:18,610
Yes.

611
00:42:33,970 --> 00:42:36,230
I'm sorry.

612
00:42:37,370 --> 00:42:39,430
I was harsh.

613
00:42:40,570 --> 00:42:43,240
But there's one thing I feel was unfair.

614
00:42:46,900 --> 00:42:49,020
That isn't how you apologize.

615
00:42:49,020 --> 00:42:50,650
How should I do it, then?

616
00:42:50,650 --> 00:42:54,060
Talk about what you did wrong, not what you thought was unfair.

617
00:42:54,060 --> 00:42:55,970
Fine.

618
00:42:55,970 --> 00:42:59,240
I'm sorry. I was harsh.

619
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:03,340
From now on, tell us if something bad happens or when you have good news.

620
00:43:03,340 --> 00:43:05,880
- Share everything. 
 - I already do.

621
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:08,630
You aren't ready to apologize.

622
00:43:12,550 --> 00:43:16,670
As far as I know, I don't have a girlfriend.

623
00:43:16,670 --> 00:43:19,210
The "Hui Joo" you speak of is probably...

624
00:43:21,750 --> 00:43:23,360
"Probably"?

625
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:27,190
Kang Hae Joon's ex-girlfriend.

626
00:43:30,740 --> 00:43:33,620
So you aren't upset with me anymore, right?

627
00:43:50,050 --> 00:43:51,620
Eat.

628
00:43:59,590 --> 00:44:01,360
It's good, right?

629
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:05,960
Aigoo, have plenty. You're just grilling.

630
00:44:07,830 --> 00:44:10,170
- I'll go ahead. 
 - Okay.

631
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:16,100
What's going on with her? Did I do something wrong?

632
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:19,210
- Hui Joo. 
 - Hui...

633
00:44:19,890 --> 00:44:21,960
What about H-Hui Joo?

634
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:27,950
She's sad you didn't tell her you had a girlfriend.

635
00:44:31,020 --> 00:44:35,230
She's realizing she and Kang Hae Joon have a shallow relationship.

636
00:44:35,230 --> 00:44:37,980
It's probably an opportunity for her to learn that.

637
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:40,320
We've been broken up for ages!

638
00:44:40,320 --> 00:44:42,820
- You told her we broke up, right? 
 - Yes.

639
00:44:42,820 --> 00:44:44,770
You told her why we broke up, right?

640
00:44:44,770 --> 00:44:46,730
Why would I tell her that? She didn't even ask.

641
00:44:46,730 --> 00:44:49,730
You should have! It was because of you!

642
00:44:49,730 --> 00:44:51,600
What?

643
00:44:53,130 --> 00:44:54,650
What?

644
00:44:57,730 --> 00:45:00,400
You called me up here. Start talking.

645
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,600
I think there has been a small misunderstanding.

646
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:04,390
It hasn't even been three months

647
00:45:04,390 --> 00:45:08,100
since you threw me out like an old shoe, saying you like Kim San Ha.

648
00:45:09,510 --> 00:45:11,960
I didn't throw you out.

649
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:13,890
Being with someone for a short time, you can't know.

650
00:45:13,890 --> 00:45:16,850
I guess San Ha could have a cute side...

651
00:45:17,930 --> 00:45:20,130
Sure, I guess.

652
00:45:20,130 --> 00:45:22,560
- Let's get back together. 
 - Hey!

653
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:23,670
Please?

654
00:45:23,670 --> 00:45:25,900
Stop. Don't make things difficult.

655
00:45:25,900 --> 00:45:28,900
You told me not to tell anyone about us,

656
00:45:28,900 --> 00:45:31,870
so I really didn't tell anyone.

657
00:45:33,750 --> 00:45:38,290
But I just got caught, so I'm in a tricky situation with Joo Won.

658
00:45:39,750 --> 00:45:41,270
Why is that tricky?

659
00:45:41,270 --> 00:45:43,510
Is there something between you and her? I thought she was your sister.

660
00:45:43,510 --> 00:45:46,910
It's a problem for me!

661
00:45:46,910 --> 00:45:49,780
I don't want to hurt her feelings.

662
00:45:49,780 --> 00:45:53,000
 She wasn't dating Kim San Ha. It was Kang Hae Joon. 

663
00:45:53,610 --> 00:45:57,230
What? Really? Are you sure?

664
00:45:57,230 --> 00:45:59,190
Why are you so surprised?

665
00:45:59,190 --> 00:46:01,690
Oh, I mean...

666
00:46:01,690 --> 00:46:03,930
I just can't see them together.

667
00:46:03,930 --> 00:46:06,420
Maybe that's why they broke up.

668
00:46:07,120 --> 00:46:09,660
- So did they break up? 
 - Yes.

669
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:14,060
Still, you must have been sad they didn't tell you.

670
00:46:14,060 --> 00:46:18,500
I'll just stay angry for today and forgive them tomorrow.

671
00:46:18,500 --> 00:46:21,040
He must have had a reason he couldn't tell me.

672
00:46:21,040 --> 00:46:22,530
True...

673
00:46:22,530 --> 00:46:25,810
There's no way he didn't have a girlfriend.

674
00:46:27,430 --> 00:46:29,330
She's pretty.

675
00:46:29,330 --> 00:46:32,360
Why would a girl like her ever date Kang Hae Joon?

676
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:43,530
Me?

677
00:46:43,530 --> 00:46:45,330
Are you looking at me?

678
00:46:46,660 --> 00:46:48,180
 You. 

679
00:47:11,460 --> 00:47:13,090
- What are you doing? 
 - Oh!

680
00:47:15,070 --> 00:47:17,730
You're always with Joo Won, right?

681
00:47:17,730 --> 00:47:20,780
Y-Yes.

682
00:47:21,640 --> 00:47:23,700
What was your name again?

683
00:47:23,700 --> 00:47:26,330
It was a really pretty name.

684
00:47:27,750 --> 00:47:28,750
   

685
00:47:28,750 --> 00:47:31,830
Oh, right! Park Dal.

686
00:47:33,690 --> 00:47:35,340
Where's Joo Won?

687
00:47:37,460 --> 00:47:39,620
Well...

688
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:49,450
- What? 
 - You're so pretty.

689
00:47:50,840 --> 00:47:53,270
I hear that a lot.

690
00:47:53,270 --> 00:47:55,510
I see it.

691
00:47:56,730 --> 00:47:59,880
You know Hae Joon and I dated briefly, right?

692
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:03,710
- Unni, it's fine! 
 - What?

693
00:48:03,710 --> 00:48:06,700
You're beautiful enough just as you are,

694
00:48:06,700 --> 00:48:09,320
and deserve to be loved.

695
00:48:10,700 --> 00:48:15,350
Kang Hae Joon's eyes must be messed up from playing basketball every day.

696
00:48:15,350 --> 00:48:19,490
- Pardon? 
 - Unni, shake it off. Understand?

697
00:48:19,490 --> 00:48:22,410
Kang Hae Joon's muscles are just for show.

698
00:48:22,410 --> 00:48:23,890
They aren't from basketball.

699
00:48:23,890 --> 00:48:27,170
He built them on purpose by doing push-ups at home.

700
00:48:27,170 --> 00:48:29,460
- It isn't– 
 - It's fine.

701
00:48:29,460 --> 00:48:31,830
He looks normal in public.

702
00:48:31,830 --> 00:48:33,000
I said it isn't like that.

703
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:35,910
If you waver now and get back with him,

704
00:48:35,910 --> 00:48:37,870
it'll be a dark chapter of your life.

705
00:48:37,870 --> 00:48:40,030
Trust me and focus on your studies.

706
00:48:40,030 --> 00:48:42,620
I dumped him!

707
00:48:43,380 --> 00:48:45,650
- What? 
 - No.

708
00:48:45,650 --> 00:48:48,160
Technically, I didn't even dump him.

709
00:48:48,160 --> 00:48:50,740
We were dating, then we took a break.

710
00:48:50,740 --> 00:48:55,130
Hae Joon misunderstood and said that I "threw him out."
    

711
00:48:55,130 --> 00:48:58,600
You threw him out?

712
00:48:59,300 --> 00:49:01,340
Who are you to throw anyone out?

713
00:49:01,340 --> 00:49:03,270
Why would you throw him out?

714
00:49:03,270 --> 00:49:06,150
Why does he have to get dumped?

715
00:49:06,150 --> 00:49:08,730
Why do you care?

716
00:49:08,730 --> 00:49:12,480
Whether Hae Joon gets dumped or not, it's his love life.

717
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:16,090
Honestly, you aren't even Hae Joon's real sister.

718
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:20,190
What angers me the most is your pretending to be his sister.

719
00:49:20,190 --> 00:49:21,510
I am his sister.

720
00:49:21,510 --> 00:49:25,790
How? Hae Joon's last name is Kang, and yours...

721
00:49:25,790 --> 00:49:28,220
is Yoon.

722
00:49:30,990 --> 00:49:34,270
That's a paperwork issue, it's not a big—

723
00:49:34,270 --> 00:49:37,510
How isn't it a big deal that you aren't family on paper?

724
00:49:37,510 --> 00:49:41,380
Didn't you learn about family units in elementary school?

725
00:49:41,380 --> 00:49:43,470
Who cares who your family is on paper?

726
00:49:43,470 --> 00:49:45,620
If you think you're family, then you are.

727
00:49:45,620 --> 00:49:49,310
Do you need a piece of paper to validate that?

728
00:49:49,310 --> 00:49:54,160
Our flesh and bones all grew eating the same rice!

729
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:56,670
If living and eating together makes you family,

730
00:49:56,670 --> 00:50:01,050
is everyone living in the same dorm all one family?

731
00:50:01,050 --> 00:50:04,600
- That's different. 
 - How so?

732
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:06,900
So, how far does a family go?

733
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:08,660
Your cousins? Because you're blood-related?

734
00:50:08,660 --> 00:50:10,370
That's right! Because we're blood-related!

735
00:50:10,370 --> 00:50:13,520
How about your step-siblings by re-marriage? Adoptees?

736
00:50:13,520 --> 00:50:16,160
Plenty of families aren't blood-related.

737
00:50:16,160 --> 00:50:20,110
Unni, do you really think those people aren't family?

738
00:50:20,110 --> 00:50:22,230
Seriously? For real?

739
00:50:22,230 --> 00:50:27,270
Don't you know how hurtful that thinking could be to those people?

740
00:50:27,270 --> 00:50:30,880
I mean, those instances are different.

741
00:50:30,880 --> 00:50:34,290
Right. Every case is different.

742
00:50:34,290 --> 00:50:36,440
I think so, too.

743
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:38,690
If we are done, I'll get going.

744
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:51,170
We aren't finished.

745
00:51:00,210 --> 00:51:01,820
Wait!

746
00:51:03,730 --> 00:51:06,500
Just wait a second.

747
00:51:17,330 --> 00:51:19,010
I'm sorry.

748
00:51:19,010 --> 00:51:20,410
What?

749
00:51:22,190 --> 00:51:27,430
I... didn't know you hated me that much.

750
00:51:28,470 --> 00:51:30,580
That's Yoon Joo Won. First year.

751
00:51:30,580 --> 00:51:31,860
The crazy one?

752
00:51:31,860 --> 00:51:34,760
She keeps insisting she's Kim San Ha and Kang Hae Joon's younger sister.

753
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:36,390
I heard that, too.

754
00:51:36,390 --> 00:51:38,550
I heard she bullies people if she doesn't like them.

755
00:51:38,550 --> 00:51:40,610
Right, right.

756
00:51:41,840 --> 00:51:45,900
No! Joo Won isn't like that.

757
00:51:52,380 --> 00:51:54,620
Stop being excessive and get up.

758
00:51:55,630 --> 00:52:00,520
I'm speaking from experience...

759
00:52:00,520 --> 00:52:03,050
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

760
00:52:03,050 --> 00:52:04,570
Get up.

761
00:52:07,010 --> 00:52:08,880
Look at your knee!

762
00:52:08,880 --> 00:52:10,410
You're bleeding!

763
00:52:10,410 --> 00:52:12,470
Look at the blood! It must hurt.

764
00:52:12,470 --> 00:52:15,040
No, I didn't do that.

765
00:52:15,040 --> 00:52:18,290
She tried to push me into the pond last time.

766
00:52:18,290 --> 00:52:20,520
She's a repeat offender.

767
00:52:20,520 --> 00:52:21,890
She should go to a disciplinary hearing.

768
00:52:21,890 --> 00:52:26,370
You're all witnesses. Understand?

769
00:52:31,180 --> 00:52:33,310
Let's go to the nurse's office first.

770
00:52:42,770 --> 00:52:46,440
So you won't apologize, right?

771
00:52:47,590 --> 00:52:50,470
There's nothing to apologize for.

772
00:52:50,470 --> 00:52:52,390
She isn't going to apologize.

773
00:52:52,390 --> 00:52:54,550
She's worse than I heard.

774
00:52:54,550 --> 00:52:57,240
So mean.

775
00:52:57,240 --> 00:53:00,030
She was like that to us, too...

776
00:53:00,930 --> 00:53:02,880
Say you're sorry.

777
00:53:11,290 --> 00:53:13,490
Sorry for what?

778
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:24,120
Did you push her?

779
00:53:24,120 --> 00:53:25,890
No, I didn't push her.

780
00:53:25,890 --> 00:53:27,690
Really.

781
00:53:31,480 --> 00:53:33,640
Who saw her push her?

782
00:53:36,330 --> 00:53:37,820
Anyone?

783
00:53:39,160 --> 00:53:44,690
Are there people who don't know about her bullying?

784
00:53:44,690 --> 00:53:46,360
What bullying?

785
00:53:47,230 --> 00:53:48,670
Falling into the pond?

786
00:53:48,670 --> 00:53:51,690
Do you want me to explain how that happened right now?

787
00:53:51,690 --> 00:53:56,470
I can report spreading rumors to bully someone as school violence, right?

788
00:53:57,520 --> 00:54:00,310
Plus, Hui Joo, you're going to Seoul National University next year.

789
00:54:00,310 --> 00:54:04,010
You wouldn't want to bother with a school violence disciplinary hearing.

790
00:54:05,720 --> 00:54:07,220
Right?

791
00:54:11,920 --> 00:54:15,340
I didn't say anything.

792
00:54:17,810 --> 00:54:19,950
Then, we are settled.

793
00:54:19,950 --> 00:54:21,550
Let's go.

794
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:28,490
♫  Back then, we were the world  ♫

795
00:54:28,490 --> 00:54:30,770
♫  Everything existed for us  ♫

796
00:54:30,770 --> 00:54:32,800
What? Say I'm sorry?

797
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:37,830
♫  Like the sun in the clearest summer sky  ♫

798
00:54:37,830 --> 00:54:47,340
♫  Those shattering days when we lived for each other  ♫

799
00:54:47,340 --> 00:54:49,560
Wow, cheonggukjang!* 
